gher than 1300?</span><hr size=1>  <br>
    People now a days have higer AC than ever.. I was just wondering if it ever gets to a point to where you dont notice it anymore.  Like would you actually get hit less if your AC is 1400 when compared to 1300? Is there a Cap on AC like other stats?  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ulaelu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Laelu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#DDA0DD>(8/11/01 8:32:22 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AC higher than 1300?</span><hr size=1> I believe the softcap was once 1000, then it was raised to 1150, but now I hear it is 1350.<br>
<br>
After 1350 the improvements are much less noticable - so I hear.<br>
<br>
We have several warriors in Heaven and Earth that can pass the 1350 mark if I am not mistaken. (full warlords, dain belt, etc)<br>
<br>
Hell, i'm an enchanter, and I can get just over 800ac..  If I get some gear upgrades in the future (desperatly need: belt, range item, helm, neck, and shoulders that aren't shit level 12 items..), then I expect I can hit 900ac with no trouble.  (Iron Scroll for range, Velk or ToV hat, BCG or Better belt, etc) I hear the record for a caster is a FoH enchanter that can pull 1000-1100ac.<br>
<br>
Its kinda sick when a 60th enchanter can tank frogs in LGuk better than a warrior could back in the day. =p <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/uainian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ainian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 136<br> <font color=#DDA0DD>(8/11/01 10:34:30 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AC higher than 1300?</span><hr size=1> Bah an Enchanter will never tank as well as a warrior regardless of AC. Sure with higher AC they will get hit for less points of damage, but they will still get hit ALOT more.<br>
Dodge, Parry, Riposte will always make sure of that <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
From what I have &quot;read&quot; the AC softcaps differ on the continent you are fighting on. Pre Kunark world the softcap is 1000, Kunark 1100, Velious there is no softcap. (Just what I have read). My AC is currently somewhere around the 1300 mark, with half a suit of Warlords and no Dain belt etc (thanks Woodelf massive Agility), but I have noticed that warriors in my guild that are pushing the 1350+ mark do seem to be able to tank alot better than me. <br>
I think somewhere you have to be able to find the balance between AC and HP items. <br>
I really think it also boil's down to what you are fighting. Example; Derakor the Vindicator (red con to me at 60) hits me for pretty much Maximum damage every attack he does on me, so I think HP items are the way to go on red con's where as if you are fighting blue con mob's AC is perhaps the way to go.<br>
Something of interest I read while trolling some of the guild's on other server boards, is that a few people claim that the damage you take from a mob is an equation of your AC vs The mob's ATK. Vice-versa for the damage you do to him. I don't know if this is true or not ( I have no way to test it ) but it is something to think about I suppose. Although this could explain that when you are fighting a red con you get hit for max the majority of the time ( Red con's will naturally have higher ATK than a blue )<br>
<br>
